              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "DIGITAL SIGNAL PROCESSING",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h3",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "A signal",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": " is defined as any physical quantity that varies with time, space, or any other independent variable or variables.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Mathematically, we describe a signal as a function of one or more independent variables.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Ex.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "s(t) = 2t² + 3t - 2\t\tSingle-Variable",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "u(x, y) = x²y – 3x + 2y\t\tMulti-Variable",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Some signals are too complicated to be represented by functions, such as speech signal (seen above). These complex signals may be represented to a high degree of accuracy as a sum of several sinusoids of different amplitudes and frequencies.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal Source",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal generation is usually associated with a system that responds to a stimulus or force. In a speech signal, the system consists of the vocal cords and the vocal tract, also called the vocal cavity. The stimulus in combination with the system is called a ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "signal source",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": ". Thus we have speech sources, images sources, and various other types of signal sources.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "System",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "A system",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": " may also be defined as a physical device that performs an operation on a signal.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "For example, a filter used to reduce the noise and interference corrupting a desired information-bearing signal is called a system. In this case the filter performs some operation(s) on the signal, which has the effect of reducing (filtering) the noise and interference from the desired information-bearing signal.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal Processing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 1,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal processing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": " is a method of extracting information from the signal which in turn depends on the type of signal and the nature of information it carries.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Signal processing is concerned with representing signals in the mathematical terms and extracting information by carrying out algorithmic operations on the signal.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Analog Signal Processing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Most of the signals encountered in science and engineering are analog in nature. In such a case we say that the signal has been processed directly in its analog form, as illustrated in the figure. Both the input signal and the output signal are in analog form.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
