            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Digital signal processing provides an alternative method for processing the analog signal, as illustrated in the figure. To perform the processing digitally, there is a need for an interface between the analog signal and the digital processor. This interface is called an analog-to-digital (A/D) converter. The output of the A/D converter is a digital signal that is appropriate as an input to the digital processor.",
