            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Advantages of Digital over Analog Processing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "There are many reasons why digital signal processing of an analog signal may be preferable to processing the signal directly in the analog domain:",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "Digital circuits do not depend on precise values of digital signals for their operation. Digital circuits are less sensitive to changes in component values. They are also less sensitive to variations in temperature, ageing and other external parameters.",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "a digital programmable system allows flexibility in reconfiguring the digital signal processing operations simply by changing the program",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "a digital system provides much better control of accuracy requirements",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "Digital signals are easily stored on magnetic media or any digital media and consequently, the signals become transportable and can be processed off-line in a remote laboratory.",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "The digital signal processing method also allows for the implementation of more sophisticated signal processing algorithms",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "In some cases, a digital implementation of the signal processing system is cheaper than its analog counterpart.",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "listType": "bullet",
            "start": 1,
            "tag": "ul",
            "type": "list",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Drawbacks of Digital Processing",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "tag": "h1",
            "type": "heading",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "There are some drawbacks associated with processing a signal in digital domain:",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "paragraph",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "Digital processing needs 'pre' and 'post' processing devices like analog-to-digital and digital-to-analog converters and associated reconstruction filters",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "Digital techniques suffer from frequency limitations.",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "detail": 0,
                    "format": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": "",
                    "text": "Digital systems are constructed using active devices which consume power whereas analog processing algorithms can be implemented using passive devices which do not consume power.",
                    "type": "text",
                    "version": 1
                  }
                ],
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "type": "listitem",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "listType": "bullet",
            "start": 1,
            "tag": "ul",
            "type": "list",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
